    "what_description": "Humulus lupulus is a perennial plant that belongs to the family Cannabaceae. It is a climbing plant with stems that can grow up to 6 meters long, bearing palmate leaves with 5-9 leaflets and small green flowers that are arranged in axillary corymbose clusters. The flowers are dioecious, with male and female flowers on separate plants, and are pollinated by bees and butterflies. The fruit is a cylindrical, 6-8 mm long achene with a single seed, attached to the plant by a persistent, 2-3 mm long pedicel. Humulus lupulus is native to Europe, Western Asia, and North Africa.",
