    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Humulus lupulus are rooted in its potent antioxidant activities, which have been attributed to the presence of flavonoids and phenolic acids, allowing it to protect against oxidative stress and cell damage. Its antimicrobial properties, mediated by sesquiterpenes and flavonoids, enable the plant to inhibit the growth of various microorganisms, thereby reducing the risk of infections. Additionally, the sedative properties of Humulus lupulus, facilitated by sesquiterpenes and essential oils, contribute to its ability to promote relaxation and reduce anxiety. The anti-inflammatory effects of the plant, attributed to sesquiterpenes and flavonoids, make it useful in reducing inflammation and alleviating pain, while its antispasmodic properties, mediated by sesquiterpenes and flavonoids, enable it to relax smooth muscle tissues and reduce spasms. The bioactive compounds responsible for these properties work synergistically to contribute to the medicinal efficacy of Humulus lupulus.",
