    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Humulus lupulus are hop oil, a volatile oil extracted from the cone's lupulin glands, containing alpha acids, responsible for the bitter flavor and preservative properties; hop extract, a concentrated form of hop cones, used in brewing and as a dietary supplement; hop tea, an infusion made from dried hop cones, traditionally used to aid sleep; lupulin tea, a tea prepared from the lupulin glands, rich in sesquiterpenes and humulone, compounds with antimicrobial and anti-inflammatory properties; hop tincture, a concentrated liquid extract of hop cones, used in herbal medicine for its sedative and anti-anxiety effects.",
