    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Humulus lupulus improperly include interactions with medications such as blood thinners, as it can inhibit the CYP3A4 enzyme, increasing the risk of bleeding and bruising. Additionally, consuming excessive amounts can induce vomiting due to its bitter compounds, such as humulone and lupulone, which can irritate the stomach lining. Furthermore, improper use can cause dizziness and lightheadedness due to its vasodilatory properties, which can lower blood pressure and reduce blood flow to the brain. Developing allergic reactions to Humulus lupulus is also a possibility, as it contains terpenoids and flavonoids that can trigger an immune response, resulting in symptoms such as hives, itching, and difficulty breathing. Lastly, consuming large quantities can cause diarrhea due to its saponin content, which can disrupt gut motility and increase water loss in the stool."
